Greetings, %PLAYERNAME%. Your arrival here is a relief.
While Professor Willow is presently engaged investigating the curious interplay of light and shadow in the park, I have been drawn to the Ultra Wormholes that opened in the sky.
I have no doubt that your assistance will prove invaluable in unraveling these perplexing occurrences and ensuring the safety of humans and Pokémon alike.
It is worth noting that similar phenomena have been reported all over the world—meaning that people from all over are looking to us for answers .
Bearing that in mind, let us cooperate to shed light on this mystery.
In the course of my investigations, I encountered two Pokémon of interest.
Please seek out this enigmatic Pokémon—I will continue my analysis of the Ultra Wormholes in the meantime.
Please seek out this enigmatic Pokémon—I will continue my analysis of the Ultra Wormholes in the meantime.
One was adorned in something peculiar, and the other was of a hue I have never witnessed before.
I assure you that your findings will prove a valuable contribution to our shared understanding.
I assure you that your findings will prove a valuable contribution to our shared understanding.
They may hold the key to comprehending the present situation.
Let us reconvene once we have made progress in our respective inquiries.
Let us reconvene once we have made progress in our respective inquiries.
Would you prefer to track one of them in particular?
%PLAYERNAME%, these Ultra Wormholes are allowing more Ultra Beasts to enter your world. And I am getting readings that suggest the presence of an immense power.
My analysis indicates that said power may originate from one of two Legendary Pokémon—Solgaleo or Lunala.
Also, I should note—I fear the abundance of light within this city could attract the attention of something even more powerful: the Prism Pokémon Necrozma, which is known to consume light itself.
Also, I should note—I fear the abundance of light within this city could attract the attention of something even more powerful: the Prism Pokémon Necrozma, which is known to consume light itself.
Which one do you think it is?
Were Necrozma’s hunger to draw it to this world, it could cause untold destruction. Please seek out Lunala, %PLAYERNAME%.
Were Necrozma’s hunger to draw it to this world, it could cause untold destruction. Please seek out Solgaleo, %PLAYERNAME%.
Forming a connection with it may prove crucial in expanding our knowledge of Necrozma.
Forming a connection with it may prove crucial in expanding our knowledge of Necrozma.
I will continue to monitor the Ultra Wormholes and gather what information I can. I promise you that if and when we encounter Necrozma, we will be ready.
I will continue to monitor the Ultra Wormholes and gather what information I can. I promise you that if and when we encounter Necrozma, we will be ready.
I have news, %PLAYERNAME%. It concerns your new partner, Lunala.
I have news, %PLAYERNAME%. It concerns your new partner, Solgaleo.
The city’s own radiance combined with the presence of Lunala has drawn the attention of the light-devouring Necrozma, just as I feared.
The city’s radiance combined with the presence of Solgaleo has drawn the attention of the light-devouring Necrozma, just as I feared.
Only you possess the skills and compassion necessary to confront and catch Necrozma.
Only you possess the skills and compassion necessary to confront and catch Necrozma.
If you’re able to forge a bond of understanding with the Prism Pokémon, we’ll be able to protect both this world and Necrozma itself.
If you’re able to forge a bond of understanding with the Prism Pokémon, we’ll be able to protect both this world and Necrozma itself.
Approach this trial with an open heart and steady hand, and I believe we will find a resolution that benefits us all—one as radiant as the light Necrozma seeks.
Approach this trial with an open heart and steady hand, and I believe we will find a resolution that benefits us all—one as radiant as the light Necrozma seeks.
%PLAYERNAME%, I must commend you for your remarkable achievement in catching Necrozma. In doing so, you have ensured the safety of both people and Pokémon the world over.
%PLAYERNAME%, I must commend you for your remarkable achievement in catching Necrozma. In doing so, you have ensured the safety of people and Pokémon the world over.
With Necrozma now in your care, I encourage you to explore the fascinating phenomenon known as fusion.
With Necrozma now in your care, I encourage you to explore the fascinating phenomenon known as fusion.
Yes—Necrozma can absorb Lunala’s light, imbuing it with immense power.
Yes—Necrozma can absorb Solgaleo’s light, imbuing it with immense power.
This is a rare opportunity to witness its metamorphosis into Dawn Wings Necrozma.
This is a rare opportunity to witness its metamorphosis into Dusk Mane Necrozma.
Your journey with the Prism Pokémon has only just begun. I am certain your skills will light the path to ever greater accomplishments.
Your journey with the Prism Pokémon has only just begun. I am certain your skills will light the path to ever greater accomplishments.
Hello there, %PLAYERNAME%! We’ve stumbled upon quite the juicy mystery here in the park.
Maybe you’ve seen flashes of light or shadows cast in unexpected places around here? It’s a real peculiar phenomenon!
And even more intriguing, these anomalies appear to move around at the drop of a hat, defying the laws of science! Not to worry, though—I’ve already cooked up a hypothesis!
But like with any good hypothesis, we need data to confirm it. That’s where you come in!
Would you be a pal and investigate these strange occurrences for me, then meet back here with your findings?
Hey, %PLAYERNAME%! Rad running into you here!
I figured this was just a secret hangout spot for the most awesome Trainers, but I’m guessing you must be looking for Professor Willow?
Y’know, I think I saw him earlier. He was skulking around all sneaky, like a Gengar playing hide-and-seek.
Pretty sure he was headed toward those habitats over there. If you hurry, you might catch him!
Oh, and tell him I said hi!
Ah, %PLAYERNAME%. I presume you are here in search of Professor Willow?
I caught sight of him earlier, but I must say, his behavior was rather peculiar. More so than usual, that is.
I only got a glimpse of him, but he was making his way through the shadows, headed in that general direction.
If either one of you uncover the cause behind what’s happening with the light and shadow around here, I would appreciate if you shared your findings.
Until then, I will continue to observe the anomalies myself. Best of luck, %PLAYERNAME%.
Heeey, %PLAYERNAME%! What brings you to this slice of the park?
Let me guess—you’re on the hunt for that elusive Marshadow too, aren’t you?
Oh, you’re looking for Professor Willow? I haven’t seen him around, but I’m totally sure I saw Marshadow earlier.
Marshadow’s a sneaky customer—loves to hide in the shadows and mimic the movements of others.
So y’know, keep your eyes peeled! You just might run into a super rare Pokémon! Good luck—oh, and don’t get spooked by the shadows!
Oh! It’s you, %PLAYERNAME%. You caught me by surprise.
Sorry for the confusion. I was on Marshadow’s trail, but it looks to me like you’ve already made its acquaintance!
I thought I was the one doing the tracking, but it turns out Marshadow was shadowing my every move. Ha!
I’m thrilled to see how quickly you’ve befriended it. This is yet another example of your exceptional skills as a Trainer.
You not only solved the mystery of the shadows, but you made yourself a powerful new friend in the process!
I see you’ve been hard at work powering up your new companion Marshadow. That’s great, but don’t forget to take a moment for yourself and enjoy the journey!
I also heard you had the pleasure of running into Spark, Blanche, and Candela. What a treat it is to run into friends unexpectedly!
Why don’t you take this opportunity to forge some new friendships, rekindle a few old ones, and embark on a grand new adventure with Marshadow at your side?
After all, life isn’t just about getting stronger. It’s about the bonds we form along the way.
I guess what I really mean to say is: thank you for your friendship, %PLAYERNAME%!

What a pleasure to see you, %PLAYERNAME%!
Go ahead and take a deep breath in! Smell that sweet scent wafting in the air?
There’s no deceiving a Pokémon Professor’s nose! That lovely aroma’s all the proof we need that the Grass-type Bounsweet must be nearby. And in great numbers, by the scent of it!
Now go on, follow your nose! Try and bring a Bounsweet back so we can study it!
I’d recognize that smell of success a mile away, %PLAYERNAME%! You’ve happened on a bounty of Bounsweet!
Here’s a fact: we’re not the only ones interested in Bounsweet. Bird Pokémon are always after them, too!
One fact isn’t enough for you? Well, did you know that Bounsweet secrete a sweet—and delicious—sweat? Now you do! I sure wish I smelled that good!
Ahem. In any event, why don’t you head out and catch some more so we can keep our sweet new friends safe?
Now that we’re acquainted with the delightful Bounsweet, let’s familiarize ourselves with its Evolution, Steenee.
Keep a sharp eye out for a Steenee performing its signature twirl. When they spin like that, they’re spreading their amazing scent far and wide.
Just a whiff will give you a surge of happiness, in fact. So what are you waiting for, %PLAYERNAME%? We’ve got joy to...well, enjoy!
But make sure you keep your guard up!
Tsareena’s kick can hit hard enough to take out even the toughest kickboxing champ.
Anyhow, thanks for all the assists today, %PLAYERNAME%. Stay sharp and keep well out of kicking distance!
Great to see you, %PLAYERNAME%! We’ve got all sorts of Pokémon to catch and research that needs doing. I can’t wait to get started!
Which of these fine feathered friends are you hoping to spot?

Greetings, %PLAYERNAME%. How fortunate to see you, though doing so under more favorable circumstances would be preferable.
Reports of Ultra Beast sightings continue to arrive, but we have yet to arrive at a conclusive explanation as to why.
On a related note, the Poipole you encountered intrigues me.
I suspect that it may be ready to evolve into Naganadel.
Naganadel is a fascinating Ultra Beast whose unique biology allows it to store hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid within its body.
I digress. The professor and I thank you for your tireless efforts thus far, %PLAYERNAME%.
We will convene again when Professor Willow and I have more information to relay.
Hello, %PLAYERNAME%! It’s good to see you. I’ve got the loveliest news to share.
One of my research colleagues recently went on an excavation and came across some unusual diamonds.
The team suspects these aren’t just any diamonds, but ones created by the Jewel Pokémon Diancie!
My colleague is sending me samples, and I’m eager to examine them further.
While we wait for them to arrive, I’ll start prepping some dazzling facts about Diancie to share!
I’m afraid the samples from my colleague are still in transit, but I promised you Diancie trivia—and I won’t keep you on the edge of your Dian-seat.
Get this: Diancie can instantly create diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
Isn’t that just phenomenal? I wonder how their color and luster compare to other diamonds...
Great work out there, %PLAYERNAME%! You’ve earned a brain-teaser: which Pokémon is Diancie a sudden transformation of?
That’s right—Carbink! Some say that deep beneath the surface of the world, a pack of Carbink live with their queen in a kingdom of jewels.
That must be an astonishing sight. Do you think that queen is Diancie?
Well, as long as we’re still waiting for the samples to arrive, why don’t you explore the area and see if you can locate a Carbink for us to observe?
Here’s something you might not know—Carbink has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth!
I sure would love to “gleam” insights from such a long-lived Pokémon.
Anyway, I was just notified that the diamond samples from my colleague should be arriving very soon.
If they’re anything like Diancie itself, prepare yourself for the loveliest sight in the world!
The samples from my colleague are finally here!
After some testing, I’ve determined that these are indeed diamonds made by Diancie. Look at that shimmer!
These diamonds are rare, but catching a glimpse of Diancie is an even more extraordinary event.
Fun fact: Diancie is a Rock- and Fairy-type Pokémon—an unusual combination indeed!
Diancie can also Mega Evolve, making it shine even more brilliantly than ever. It really is one devastatingly dazzling Pokémon.
Thanks for helping me research Carbink and Diancie!
I always treasure our time together.
We may have spent the day discussing the glitz and glamor of a Mythical Pokémon, but you’re no less of a gem yourself.
